{"title": "Consolation of Philosophy", "description": "The Consolation of Philosophy was written about 524 A.D. and has been called one of the most popular and influential books ever written. The book is presented as a dialogue between Boethius, the author, and Lady Philosophy, his tutor. Through her teaching, Boethius learns the true nature of fortune, misfortune, wealth, good, and evil.<br><br>This dramatic reading is an attempt to present this wonderful work in an audio format while maintaining the dialogic structure of the work. (Devorah Allen)<br><br><b>Cast List</b><br>Boethius, the Narrator: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/8425\">Larry Wilson</a><br>Philosophy: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/11084\">Devorah Allen</a><br>Headings and Footnotes: <a href=\"https://librivox.org/reader/13278\">KevinS</a>", "duration": 16866, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "4104", "name": " Anicius Manlius Severinus Boethius"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/consolationofphilosophy_2008_librivox/consolation_philosophy_2008.jpg", "copyright_year": "1933", "genres": ["Classics (Greek & Latin Antiquity)", "Ancient"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Devorah Allen"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Leni"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Book 1", "readers": [], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/consolationofphilosophy_2008_librivox/consolationofphilosophy_01_boethius_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2373}, {"section": 2, "title": "Book 2", "readers": [], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/consolationofphilosophy_2008_librivox/consolationofphilosophy_02_boethius_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3096}, {"section": 3, "title": "Book 3, part 1", "readers": [], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/consolationofphilosophy_2008_librivox/consolationofphilosophy_03_boethius_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1846}, {"section": 4, "title": "B